Implemented Vercel Web Analytics for Next.js

Summary:
Successfully installed and configured @vercel/analytics for the Next.js App Router project.

Changes Made:

1. Installed Dependencies:
   - Added @vercel/analytics package to the project
   - Updated package.json with the new dependency
   - Updated package-lock.json with all dependency resolutions

2. Modified Files:
   - src/app/layout.tsx:
     * Added import statement for Analytics component from '@vercel/analytics/next'
     * Added <Analytics /> component inside the <body> tag, after the Providers and TranslationProvider wrapper
     * Placed it at the end of the body to ensure optimal loading behavior

Implementation Details:
- Project Type: Next.js App Router (using app directory)
- Package Manager: npm
- Analytics Component Location: Root layout file (src/app/layout.tsx)
- The Analytics component is placed after {children} and all other content, following Vercel's best practices

Verification:
✓ Build completed successfully (npm run build)
✓ No linting errors introduced in modified files
✓ All files staged with git (package.json, package-lock.json, src/app/layout.tsx)

The implementation follows Next.js App Router conventions and Vercel's recommended setup for Web Analytics. The analytics will automatically track page views and web vitals when deployed to Vercel.
